o migrated from the Korna Mountains to the area later became their place of residence.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Cultural Heritage, Handicrafts and Tourism Organization of Iran]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghatreh.com/news/nn30924460/\u0639\u06a9\u0633-\u062d\u0645\u0627\u0645-\u06a9\u0631\u0646\u0627\u0633\u06cc\u0627\u0646-\u062f\u0632\u0641\u0648\u0644-\u0622\u062a\u0634|title=\u0631\u0647\u06cc\u0627\u0628 \u0646\u06cc\u0648\u0632|website=\u0645\u0648\u062a\u0648\u0631 \u062c\u0633\u062a\u062c\u0648\u06cc \u0642\u0637\u0631\u0647|language=fa|access-date=2019-09-05}}</ref>\n\n{{Iran topics}}\n{{Khuzestan Province}}\n{{Authority control}}\n__NOTOC__\n__INDEX__\n\n[[Category:National Works of Iran]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox historic site\n| name = Bathroom Kornasian\n| native_name = \u062d\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u06a9\u0631\u0646\u0627\u0633\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \n| native_language = Persian\n| native_name2 = \u062d\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u06a9\u0631\u0646\u0627\u0633\u06cc\u0648\u0646\n| native_language2 = Persian\n| native_name3 = \n| native_language3 = \n| other_name = * [[Haj Nasir Bath]]\n* [[New bathroom]]\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| alt = A historic place in [[Dezful]]\n| caption = \n| locmapin = \n| map_relief = \n| map_width = 150px\n| map_caption = Local in Map\n| map_dot_mark = \n| coordinates = <!-- {{Coord}} -->\n| gbgridref = \n| gbgridref_note =\n| type = * [[Bathroom]]\n| etymology = \n| location = {{Maplink|frame=yes|plain=yes|frame-width=250|frame-height=280|zoom=8|frame-lat=29.185|frame-long=76.225\n|type=shape-inverse|id=Q605142|title=dezful\n|type2=point|id2=Q5877097|stroke-width=3|title2=Bathroom Kornasian\n}}\n| nearest_city = \n| area = \n| elevation = \n| height = \n| beginning_label = \n| beginning_date = \n| formed = \n| founded = \n| founder = \n| built = [[Zand dynasty]]\n| built_for = [[Qajar dynasty]]\n| original_use = \n| demolished = \n| rebuilt = 1903 to 2006 